cs.DS, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a model and framework for algorithm design on GPUs, specifically for sorting algorithms. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of shared memory and memory banks in GPU architecture. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper focuses on parallel algorithm design for GPUs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of algorithms in the context of GPU programming. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to develop provably efficient GPU algorithms.
